&lt;h3 id=&#34;onsubmit&#34;&gt;onSubmit&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is a function of a simple form that performs a list of actions. It is called when the form is submitted.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To submit a form, you must use the SubmitForm action and call it, just implement it in a &lt;a href=&#34;../ui/button.md&#34;&gt;Button&lt;/a&gt; that is part of a simple form, that is, that is in your list of children.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When you click this button, the onSubmit is activated and the list of actions will be performed. It is this list of actions that will define what should happen with the information in this form, if they will be sent to a backend (through the &lt;a href=&#34;../../actions/sendrequest.md&#34;&gt;sendRequest &lt;/a&gt;action), etc.&lt;/p&gt;
